result.name: 1979-1979-centre-for-environment-fisheries-aquaculture-science-cefas-1979-eastern-irish-sea-gro
result.notes:
A series of groundfish surveys were carried out on the fishing vessel Silver 
Star from 1976 to 1991 in the eastern Irish Sea. Fishing took place using a 
Boris Goshawk trawl towed for an hour. This data is from the 3 surveys carried 
out during 1979. Numbers at length by centimetre of the main commercial fish 
species are recorded. Station positions by area are recorded.
